value.value: 子宮内膜欠如

any structural anomaly of the head segment of the sperm cell which contains the nucleus with densely coiled chromatin fibers, and is surrounded anteriorly by the acrosome which contains enzymes used for penetrating the female egg
尖体剥離

精子頭部矮小化

a sperm head that is unusually oblong in shape and much smaller than normal; typically, pinhead sperm result when the centrioles from which the sperm tails develop are not correctly aligned opposite the developing acrosome so that sperm heads are lost and absorbed during epididymal transit
精子鞭毛捻転

細い精子鞭毛

ヘアピン精子鞭毛

精巣上体頭部肥大

definition.value: Note that a thymocyte is an immature T cell located in the thymus (CL:0000893).
